Config:
REALTIME_ENABLED=true
REALTIME_EVENT_BUFFER_SIZE=500
NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=true
NOTIFICATION_DRY_RUN=true
ALERT_RULES_ENABLED=true
EMAIL_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=false
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=
SMTP_PASSWORD=
SMTP_FROM=
WEBHOOK_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=false
WEBHOOK_URL=

Realtime endpoint:
WS /api/realtime/events

Features:
- Auth via token query param or Authorization-compatible handshake.
- Tenant-scoped event stream.
- Sends recent buffered events on connect.
- Streams new events live.
- Supports event category filter.
- Sends heartbeat ping.
- Cleans up disconnected clients.

Event categories:
system, agent, trading, risk, scheduler, worker, iot, backtest, content, auth, audit, notification

AlertRule:
id, organization_id, workspace_id, name, event_type, severity, enabled, condition, channels, created_at, updated_at

AlertEvent:
id, organization_id, workspace_id, rule_id, severity, title, message, payload, status, created_at

NotificationChannel:
id, organization_id, workspace_id, name, channel_type, enabled, config, created_at, updated_at

Channel types:
dry_run, email, webhook

Default alert rules:
- risk emergency stop triggered
- risk halt activated
- worker task failed
- scheduler job failed
- content publish blocked
- IoT action blocked
- auth login failure spike
- production safety blocker

Notification service:
- In dry-run mode, record notification but do not send.
- Email channel stubbed unless SMTP configured.
- Webhook channel stubbed unless WEBHOOK_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=true.
- Never send secrets in notification payloads.

APIs:
GET    /api/notifications/status
GET    /api/notifications/rules
POST   /api/notifications/rules
PATCH  /api/notifications/rules/{rule_id}
DELETE /api/notifications/rules/{rule_id}
GET    /api/notifications/events
GET    /api/notifications/channels
POST   /api/notifications/channels
PATCH  /api/notifications/channels/{channel_id}
DELETE /api/notifications/channels/{channel_id}
POST   /api/notifications/test

Rules:
- Auth required.
- Tenant scoped.
- Admin/operator can manage rules and channels.
- Viewer/analyst can read alert events.
- Audit all changes.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

